    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT354-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">parattaiyiṟ pirintu vāyil vēṇaṭic ceṉṟa talaimakaṟkut tōḻi vāyiṉ
          maṟuttatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The door refused by the confidante to HIM, who went
          wishing for the door, after having separated on account of another woman. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT354">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> nīrnī ṭāṭiṟ kaṇṇuñ civakku</l>
          <l> mārntōr vāyiṟ ṟēṉum puḷikkun</l>
          <l> taṇantaṉai yāyiṉem milluyttuk koṭumō</l>
          <l> vantaṇ poykai yentai yemmūrk</l>
          <l> kaṭumpāmpu vaḻaṅkun teruvi</l>
          <l> ṉaṭuṅkaña revvaṅ kaḷainta vemmē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>When playing in water for long the eyes will redden</l>
          <l>and in the mouth of one satisfied even <note place="foot"> Here we presumably have to assume a double function of  <term xml:lang="ta"> -um </term>, coordination and enumeration. </note> honey will turn sour.<note place="foot">This obvious aphoristic prelude of two lines is not particle-marked. It would also be possible to read a <term xml:lang="ta"> peyareccam</term> clause in causal function: "since [as is known] ... turns sour". </note> </l>
          <l>When you are departed, send us back to our house,</l>
          <l rend="indent">for whom [you once] had removed the trouble of trembling sorrow,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">in a street where quick snakes wander,<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta"> kaṭum pāmpu vaḻaṅkum teruvil</term>: is this supposed to denote the danger HE undergoes by coming? Or is it to be read as a metonymic apposition: "in the street, a quickly wandering snake", i.e. a meandering road? </note> </l>
          <l rend="indent3">in our village, at my father's, by the pretty cool pond.</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="3b">
            <l>If you should depart, send [us] back to our house</l>
          </lg>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
